usage:

 vp [args] < datafile

 optional args are:

  --format=ascii (default) [shortcut: -f a]
    ascii, with header line
    first line contains attribute names, whitespace delimited
    additional lines each contain all numeric attribute values for one sample, whitespace delimited

  --format=binary [shortcut: -f b]
    one line of ascii attribute names, whitespace delimited, ending with newline (\n);
    immediately followed by raw table of binary floating point values

  --npoints=<integer> [shortcut: -n <int>] (default all)
    number of datapoints (samples, rows in file) to read.  

  --rows=<integer> [shortcut: -r <int>] (default 2)
    number of rows of scatterplots

  --cols=<integer> [shortcut: -c <int>] (default 2)
    number of columns of scatterplots

  --bordeless [shortcut: -b]
    attempt to maximize plot windows' usable area by removing window manager decorations.
    note: this seems to cause problems with keyboard shortcuts in plot windows on OSX

  --help [shortcut: -h]
    print short help message.


Keys & Buttons (in plot windows):

  action		key
  ------		----
  new selection		left-mouse
  move selection	left-mouse + shift
  invert selection	i
  display deselected 	d
  clear selection	c
  kill selected points	x
  reset view		r
  quit			q


Mouse Gestures (in plot windows):

  action		gesture
  ------		-------
  select points		left-mouse
  translate		right-mouse  (opt-mouse on OSX)
  scale			middle-mouse (ctl-mouse on OSX)
  scale histogram	middle-mouse + h (ctl-mouse + h on OSX)


Controls in control panels:

  control	action
  ------	------
  npoints	number of points displayed
  alpha		point opacity.
  lum		point brightness
  bkg		background color (try bkg=0.5, lum=0.2)
  size		point size, in pixels
  nbins		number of histogram bins
  rot		rotation angle in 3D (please select something for the 3rd axis to display)
  spin		continuous rotation
  sum vs. diff	plot (x+y) vs. (x-y)
  polar		x<-r, y<-theta

Normalizations (per axis)

  none		show all data, center of window at median
  zeromax	show all positive data
  maxabs	show all data, center of window at zero
  threesigma	center of window at sample mean, window spans +/- three sigma.
  rank		plot rank of x (instead of x)
                  (i.e. nonuniform rescaling to force uniform marginal)
  gaussianize	plot inverse of Gaussian cummulative distribution function of x
  		  (i.e. nonuniform rescaling to force Gaussian marginal)

